# Progress Notes Rule

## Location

- Save progress notes in `docs/progress/`.
- Keep one file per session using `YYYY-MM-DD-topic.md`.

## When to add notes

- Add a brief note after substantial code or config changes.
- Add a note any time the user explicitly requests one.
- Skip notes for trivial reads, quick answers, or no-op changes.

## What to include

Keep entries concise and outcome-focused:

- Objective
- Scope (key files)
- Changes
- Validation (only commands actually run)
- Risks or blockers
- Next actions

